{"actual_usd":0.15863500000000003,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":184,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31175,"reply":"\"I think yes — but I'd hold it carefully.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the morning light is catching on the stone.* \"Not in the sense that death stops hurting, or that you have to pretend the grave is already empty by force. More like this: if you're in Christ, then even now the thing killing you does not get final say, and new life can already be breaking in before the whole story looks risen.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb against the edge of the folded note in my pocket, thinking.* \"I'd probably say you're not wrong to speak resurrection in the present tense, as long as you leave room for the fact that some of it still feels like dying. That's the honest miracle, isn't it? Not fake triumph — real life starting to grow right in the wound.\"\n\n\"What kind of death does it feel like, if you can name it plain?\"","rolling_24h_usd":67.14009999999999,"run_id":"2f5583a1-5d12-485e-af1a-4bd67cac4c5a"}
